argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong><em>Bill Cohan</em></strong><strong>: K=
im, it=E2=80=99s been
accepted wisdom for a while that there=E2=80=99s going to be a massive real=
ignment of the big players in Hollywood, which is underway, and not every l=
egacy studio will survive=E2=80=A6=C2=A0</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;m=
argin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>K=
im Masters</em>: We=E2=80=99ve already seen Fox disappear into the Disney m=
aw. Paramount was a melting ice cube before <strong>David</strong> <strong>=
Ellison</strong> stepped in. What can he do with it? We=E2=80=99ll have to =
wait and
see. But the ones that look most likely to survive are Comcast and Disney.<=
/p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">Warners being vulnerable would have been unthinkable 10=
 years ago. That Warners could become subsumed like Fox is now=E2=80=94I=E2=
=80=99m not talking about their <strong>Lachlan</strong>-controlled busines=
ses, I=E2=80=99m talking about the studio operations, which are a label at =
Disney now=E2=80=94would have been unthinkable. But a lot of people in Holl=
ywood have
been speculating for quite a while that, ultimately, <strong>Zaslav</strong=
> does make a deal with someone, maybe Comcast.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;mar=
gin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong=
>Whenever I write that a deal between WBD and NBCU is a real possibility, t=
he folks at Comcast tell me I=E2=80=99m crazy.</strong></p><p style=3D"marg=
in:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"=
>Well, you may be nuts, but that doesn=E2=80=99t stop Hollywood from
thinking about it. What that reveals is they=E2=80=99re sensing a deal of s=
ome kind.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>That both parties could benefit=
 from, frankly.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0=
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Which marriage would make the =
most beautiful couple? Clearly, we have Comcast=E2=80=99s SpinCo awaiting a=
 partner. Paramount+ maybe? David Ellison has a spinco problem too=E2=80=94=
his own
albatross to deal with. On the one hand, he has the bottomless pockets of h=
is father. On the other, we have seen many times how quickly Hollywood can =
burn money. Nobody would be surprised to see the troubled cable parts of Pa=
ramount get spun off and partnered up somewhere. We know that Zaslav went a=
nd talked to <strong>Bob</strong> <strong>Bakish</strong> before the Elliso=
n deal got stitched up, and obviously before Bakish got fired. So, he was e=
yeballing that place.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><str=
