bottom:32px;"><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;In=
ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Last topic: Can streaming and theater e=
xhibition ever
co-exist again?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0=
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">When have we seen a movie that=
 launched on a streamer become a cultural event? Take, for instance, <em>Ha=
rry Potter</em>, and all that flowed from it. It was an event as a book, bu=
t there was also an event with multiple movies and theme park attractions. =
Does that come out of a streamer? At one point, Chapek was putting a lot of=
 the movies on the streamer, and people were getting
mad. I asked him what movie succeeded there enough to really activate the D=
isney I.P. machine: to give you the theme park attraction, lunch boxes, all=
 of that cultural-impact stuff that makes your kid want to buy this, that, =
and the other. And he said <em>Encanto</em>. But it had opened in theaters=
=E2=80=A6 That=E2=80=99s one of the smart things that Zaslav said, =E2=80=
=9CWe=E2=80=99re not doing movies for the streamer.=E2=80=9D And I thought,=
 <em>No shit</em>=E2=80=94unless it=E2=80=99s a very small movie.=C2=A0=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Netf=
lix is still spending, though it=E2=80=99s dialed back. But even if people =
don=E2=80=99t run to the theater to see a movie, when it later comes on the=
 streamer, they think, =E2=80=9COh, yeah, I wanted to see that.=E2=80=9D It=
 creates a profile for it, and then, with luck, there=E2=80=99s excitement.=
 You can=E2=80=99t replace that.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-botto=
m:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>So, are =
you sanguine or concerned
about the future of Hollywood?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">You start from =
the premise that stories want to be told and will be told, in my opinion, a=
nd that=E2=80=99s a constant. We=E2=80=99re going through this incredible t=
ransformation, and it hasn=E2=80=99t even begun to take effect. A.I. is mov=
ing along at the speed of light or faster, and we don=E2=80=99t fully get w=
hat it=E2=80=99s going to do in terms of entertainment. So everything is ch=
anging, and we
can=E2=80=99t really foresee how. I mean, it=E2=80=99s conventional wisdom =
to say you=E2=80=99ll have Amazon, the Big Tech companies, plus Disney and =
Comcast. You know, those will be the survivors. That=E2=80=99s something a =
lot of people will tell you.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Zaz, of course, =
includes Warners in that mix.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-botto=
m:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Maybe, but the c=
onventional
wisdom is that he=E2=80=99s looking for a deal, which may or may not ensure=
 the survival of Warners.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"=
>=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Hollywood is not like i=
t used to be. This is a conversation I have with the old-guard Hollywood pe=
ople every other day. They say, <em>We were here for the fun part</em>. And=
 it=E2=80=99s true. It wasn=E2=80=99t necessarily fun if you were a woman, =
but we lived in an era where <strong>David</strong> <strong>Geffen</strong>
and <strong>Jeffrey</strong> <strong>Katzenberg</strong> and <strong>Barry<=
/strong> <strong>Diller</strong>, none of whom had the patience for college=
, became kings. That can=E2=80=99t happen today. You have to have some kind=
 of advanced degree to work in the CAA mailroom. It=E2=80=99s just a comple=
tely different environment.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px=
;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">The independents are going to have thei=
r hands full, but they are always fighting against all odds to make
independent films. So Hollywood, in some shape or form, I think, endures. B=
ut I don=E2=80=99t know if it=E2=80=99s the same or if it ever gets back to=
 being fun.</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
